<li id="Ch1.I4.i2" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_enumerate">2.</span> 
<div id="Ch1.I4.i2.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p id="Ch1.I4.i2.p1.1" class="ltx_p">Give a proof of the looping lemma and the classification of looping
programs given in the technical summary. This may be done using the
form of a general state-change operator (given above) or by modifying
Proof 2 of the <span id="Ch1.I4.i2.p1.1.1" class="ltx_text ltx_font_smallcaps">poly</span> closing theorem of subsection 1.2.2. Give bounds
for the “fixed distances” specified in the boundedness part in terms of
the instructions in the basic loop.</p>
</div></li>
