<li id="Ch1.I4.i11" class="ltx_item" style="list-style-type:none;"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_enumerate">11.</span> 
<div id="Ch1.I4.i11.p1" class="ltx_para">
<p id="Ch1.I4.i11.p1.1" class="ltx_p">When we summarize turtle paths as state-change operators, the
closed paths are precisely those operators that leave the turtle’s state
unchanged. This suggests the generalization of studying operators that,
when run twice (or three times, and so on), leave the state unchanged.
Describe the paths corresponding to these operators. [A]</p>
</div></li>
