<p id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2" class="ltx_p">for it is easy to see that the LCM must contain at least four factors
of 2 (from <span class="MathJax_Preview" style="color: inherit;"></span><span class="MathJax" id="MathJax-Element-1784-Frame"><nobr><span class="math ltx_Math" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m1.1" aria-label="A" role="math" style="width: 0.824em; display: inline-block;"><span style="display: inline-block; position: relative; width: 0.619em; height: 0px; font-size: 126%;"><span style="position: absolute; clip: rect(3.082em 1000.003em 4.177em -999.997em); top: -3.965em; left: 0.003em;"><span class="mrow" id="MathJax-Span-4178"><span class="semantics" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m1.1a"><span class="mi" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m1.1.1" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m1.1.1.cmml" style="font-family: STIXGeneral-Italic;">A</span></span></span><span style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; height: 3.972em;"></span></span></span><span style="border-left-width: 0.004em; border-left-style: solid; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 0px; height: 1.039em; vertical-align: -0.082em;"></span></span></nobr></span><script type="math/mml" id="MathJax-Element-1784">&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m1.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="A" display="inline"&gt;&lt;semantics id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m1.1a"&gt;&lt;mi id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m1.1.1" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m1.1.1.cmml"&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m1.1b"&gt;&lt;ci id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m1.1.1"&gt;A&lt;/ci&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m1.1c"&gt;A&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;</script>), one factor of 5 (from 360), and two factors of 3 (from
either <span class="MathJax_Preview" style="color: inherit;"></span><span class="MathJax" id="MathJax-Element-1785-Frame"><nobr><span class="math ltx_Math" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m2.1" aria-label="A" role="math" style="width: 0.824em; display: inline-block;"><span style="display: inline-block; position: relative; width: 0.619em; height: 0px; font-size: 126%;"><span style="position: absolute; clip: rect(3.082em 1000.003em 4.177em -999.997em); top: -3.965em; left: 0.003em;"><span class="mrow" id="MathJax-Span-4182"><span class="semantics" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m2.1a"><span class="mi" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m2.1.1" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m2.1.1.cmml" style="font-family: STIXGeneral-Italic;">A</span></span></span><span style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; height: 3.972em;"></span></span></span><span style="border-left-width: 0.004em; border-left-style: solid; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 0px; height: 1.039em; vertical-align: -0.082em;"></span></span></nobr></span><script type="math/mml" id="MathJax-Element-1785">&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m2.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="A" display="inline"&gt;&lt;semantics id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m2.1a"&gt;&lt;mi id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m2.1.1" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m2.1.1.cmml"&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m2.1b"&gt;&lt;ci id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m2.1.1.cmml" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m2.1.1"&gt;A&lt;/ci&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m2.1c"&gt;A&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;</script> or 360), and from this we derive that <span class="MathJax_Preview" style="color: inherit;"></span><span class="MathJax" id="MathJax-Element-1786-Frame"><nobr><span class="math ltx_Math" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m3.1" aria-label="n" role="math" style="width: 0.619em; display: inline-block;"><span style="display: inline-block; position: relative; width: 0.482em; height: 0px; font-size: 126%;"><span style="position: absolute; clip: rect(3.356em 1000.003em 4.177em -999.997em); top: -3.965em; left: 0.003em;"><span class="mrow" id="MathJax-Span-4186"><span class="semantics" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m3.1a"><span class="mi" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m3.1.1" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m3.1.1.cmml" style="font-family: STIXGeneral-Italic;">n</span></span></span><span style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; height: 3.972em;"></span></span></span><span style="border-left-width: 0.004em; border-left-style: solid; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 0px; height: 0.78em; vertical-align: -0.082em;"></span></span></nobr></span><script type="math/mml" id="MathJax-Element-1786">&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m3.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="n" display="inline"&gt;&lt;semantics id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m3.1a"&gt;&lt;mi id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m3.1.1" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m3.1.1.cmml"&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m3.1b"&gt;&lt;ci id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m3.1.1.cmml" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m3.1.1"&gt;n&lt;/ci&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m3.1c"&gt;n&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;</script> = 5 and <span class="MathJax_Preview" style="color: inherit;"></span><span class="MathJax" id="MathJax-Element-1787-Frame"><nobr><span class="math ltx_Math" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m4.1" aria-label="R" role="math" style="width: 0.824em; display: inline-block;"><span style="display: inline-block; position: relative; width: 0.619em; height: 0px; font-size: 126%;"><span style="position: absolute; clip: rect(3.082em 1000.003em 4.177em -999.997em); top: -3.965em; left: 0.003em;"><span class="mrow" id="MathJax-Span-4190"><span class="semantics" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m4.1a"><span class="mi" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m4.1.1" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m4.1.1.cmml" style="font-family: STIXGeneral-Italic;">R</span></span></span><span style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; height: 3.972em;"></span></span></span><span style="border-left-width: 0.004em; border-left-style: solid; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 0px; height: 1.039em; vertical-align: -0.082em;"></span></span></nobr></span><script type="math/mml" id="MathJax-Element-1787">&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m4.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="R" display="inline"&gt;&lt;semantics id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m4.1a"&gt;&lt;mi id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m4.1.1" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m4.1.1.cmml"&gt;R&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m4.1b"&gt;&lt;ci id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m4.1.1.cmml" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m4.1.1"&gt;R&lt;/ci&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m4.1c"&gt;R&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;</script> = 2.
So <span id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.1" class="ltx_text ltx_font_smallcaps">poly 100 144</span> has fivefold symmetry (it consists of <span class="MathJax_Preview" style="color: inherit;"></span><span class="MathJax" id="MathJax-Element-1788-Frame"><nobr><span class="math ltx_Math" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m5.1" aria-label="n" role="math" style="width: 0.619em; display: inline-block;"><span style="display: inline-block; position: relative; width: 0.482em; height: 0px; font-size: 126%;"><span style="position: absolute; clip: rect(3.356em 1000.003em 4.177em -999.997em); top: -3.965em; left: 0.003em;"><span class="mrow" id="MathJax-Span-4194"><span class="semantics" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m5.1a"><span class="mi" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m5.1.1" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m5.1.1.cmml" style="font-family: STIXGeneral-Italic;">n</span></span></span><span style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; height: 3.972em;"></span></span></span><span style="border-left-width: 0.004em; border-left-style: solid; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 0px; height: 0.78em; vertical-align: -0.082em;"></span></span></nobr></span><script type="math/mml" id="MathJax-Element-1788">&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m5.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="n" display="inline"&gt;&lt;semantics id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m5.1a"&gt;&lt;mi id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m5.1.1" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m5.1.1.cmml"&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m5.1b"&gt;&lt;ci id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m5.1.1.cmml" xref="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m5.1.1"&gt;n&lt;/ci&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="Ch1.S3.SS7.p5.2.m5.1c"&gt;n&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;</script> = 5 identical
pieces identically hooked together) and rotation number 2.</p>
